<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880930-0037 </DOCNO><HL> Who's News: Ranieri Wilson andamp; Co. </HL><SO> </SO><CO> WNEWS </CO><DATELINE> RANIERI WILSON andamp; Co. (New York)  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Richard W. Beatty joined this investment firm as director of investment banking with responsibility for coordinating investment banking advisory work. Mr. Beatty, 38 years old, had been a senior vice president in the corporate finance department of E.F. Hutton andamp; Co. At Ranieri, his work primarily will comprise merger and acquisition assignments involving financial-services firms. Lewis Ranieri, a principal in the firm, pioneered the market for mortgage-backed securities at Salomon Inc., before he was fired in the wake of personality and policy clashes in 1987. </TEXT></DOC>